<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-07-07T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-07-07T08:00:00-05:00" n="1042" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1042">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">853.84/12: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Portugal</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Magruder</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Lisbon</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-07-07T14:00:00+01:00">July 7, 1931—2
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received July 7—12:05 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>21. Decree of July 1st extends national treatment in respect of maritime
                            and port dues to foreign merchant vessels but creates new tonnage dues
                            of one escudo per gross registered ton thereby discriminating against
                            all vessels other than those discharging or loading full cargoes to the
                            manifest advantage of Portuguese bottoms. Text by mail.<note n="5" xml:id="d1042fn5">Not printed.</note> Please inform Commerce.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Magruder</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>